  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add minced garlic and onion, sauté for about 2 minutes until fragrant and soft.",
    "Gently stir-fry dumplings on high heat to seal them up slightly.",
    "Pour in condensed milk, honey or maple syrup, and water into the pan. Stir well.",
    "Simmer for another 5-7 minutes until the sauce thickens and it coats the dumplings nicely.",
    "Season with salt if needed.",
    "Serve hot."
